    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this shortfall is accepted based on regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 single-condition protocols and does not undermine the overall credibility determination. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%) across both test laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU.",
